      "content": "i get that, it's more about adaptation. but if we look at history, doesn't it seem like the \"civilized\" models—the ones with the big cities and written laws—are basically the standard we measure success by? like, when we look at the development of humanity, it feels like the path leads toward the way Western societies are structured. do you think some cultures are just naturally further along that path of development than others?",
